snippet.title: Passing Afternoon-A Tribute To Amber
snippet.description:
After watching "Wilsons Heart" the finale of season 4 of House, and how Amber died, I knew I would have to make her a tribute video-this is that video! 

I never exactly hated Amber, but I never loved her. This is a little vieo I made that shows clips of her in the past as well as the hospital scene, the crash and death, and when she saved House.

I heard Passing Afternoon, and I knew this would be the song I used the video too. For one I liked it, and for another, this was the song that played when Amber saved House.



****** Disclaimer- I do not own House, or any actors, or the clips. 

Thanks to Kate J. for the ending of Wilsons Heart



Enjoy my tribute to Amber.


EDIT:

Oh yeah, I forgot to add, some of the clips were STUBBRON... so thats why they stopped for like 3 seconds and then worked... 

not everything was coorperative for me...

snippet.title: Amber Disi-sais Part 2 (Tribute Story Song)
snippet.description:
"AMBER DISI-SAIS PART 2"

Sa pagkakataong to ano kayang nararamdaman nya? Ano kayang gusto nyang sabihin? Ano kayang gusto nyang ikuwento satin? Ano kayang mensahe nya para sa lahat ng nagmamahal sa kanya? 

Sa pangalawang pagkakataong sumulat ako ng awit para sayo idol sinubukan kong ilagay yung sarili ko sayo para makapagkuwento at makapag-pasalamat sa lahat ng nagmamahal sayo. Para sayo to Disi-sais! Sana nagugustuhan mo yung mga awiting alay ko para sayo.

Muli, nakikiramay po ako ng lubos sa pamilya at lahat ng naiwan ni Amber.

snippet.title: 311 - Amber - Chad Sexton Tribute HD Drum Cover (1080p/60fps)
snippet.description: I first heard 311 in 1998. I was in middle school and it was an awesome time in my life. I was just beginning to play drums in the school band and I was discovering lots of new music. As soon as I heard Chad play drums I thought to myself, one day I want to be that good. He had that super tight style with an amazing sounding kit. So here we are 23 years later. A huge influence to me as a young drummer and I still love to play 311 on the drums. Seen them live 4-5 times and they put on a hell of a show. I hope I did it some justice. Thank you Chad!
